      "text": [
        " قُلْتُ الصَّائِمُ يَمْضَغُ الْعِلْكَ قَالَ لَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I said, ‘The Fasting-one, can he chew the gum?’ He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘No’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "1. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about a man who chews chewing gum when fasting. He (the Imam) said, ‘No, he cannot do so.’” "
        ]
      }
